<P>
ARAFAT BACKING PERES AS ISRAELI LEADER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROME 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PLO Chairman Yasser Arafat said Thursday he has asked Arab deputies in the 
Israeli Parliament to back Labor Party leader Shimon Peres in his battle to 
form a government. 
</P>
<P>
Italian officials said the Palestine Liberation Organization leader, visiting 
Italy, told Prime Minister Giulio Andreotti: "I have asked Arab deputies 
present in the Knesset (Parliament) to vote for Peres." 
</P>
<P>
The officials said Andreotti urged Arafat to help Peres form a Cabinet for the 
sake of peace talks. 
</P>
<P>
Peres has said he is ready to form a government to replace the national unity 
Cabinet, led by the Likud Party, which fell last month in a dispute over a U.S. 
plan for Israeli-Palestinian talks. Peres backs the plan, while Likud leader 
Yitzhak Shamir opposes it. Parliament is expected to vote on the new government 
soon. 
</P>
<P>
Arafat is basking in a red-carpet welcome from Italy's top leaders that has 
provoked angry protests from Israel and Jewish groups. On Wednesday, those 
groups also protested his meeting in Paris with former President Jimmy Carter. 
