<HEADLINE>
<P>
4 SOUTH BAY GIRLS MAKE DIVISION TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four South Bay players, including two from West Torrance High School, have been 
named to the All-Southern Section Division II girls basketball team by members 
of the First Interstate Bank/Amateur Athletic Foundation board of 
sportswriters. 
</P>
<P>
West Torrance guard Rosa Olloque and North Torrance center Laura Collins were 
repeat selections on the All-Division II first team. 
</P>
<P>
Junior guard Lily Cabaleiro of Bishop Montgomery also made the squad. 
</P>
<P>
West guard Mary Litzenberg earned second-team honors. 
</P>
<P>
Olloque averaged 22 points a game, leading West to a second-place finish behind 
Morningside in the Ocean League and a berth in the Southern Section 4-A finals. 
The Warriors lost to La Quinta of Westminster, 72-62, in the title game. 
</P>
<P>
Collins, a 6-foot senior who signed early with UCLA, averaged 25.1 points and 
15.4 rebounds to lead North to a third-place finish in the Ocean League and a 
spot in the 4-A quarterfinals. She was the Most Outstanding Player in the 
league. 
</P>
<P>
Cabaleiro was the floor leader for surprising Bishop Montgomery, which reached 
the 4-A semifinals after finishing second in the Angelus League. The 5-6 point 
guard averaged 16.4 points. 
</P>
<P>
Litzenberg, Olloque's back-court mate at West, averaged 16 points a game and 
was the Warriors' leading rebounder and three-point shooter. 
</P>
<P>
Amy Jalewalia, a 6-1 center for 4-A champion La Quinta, was named Division II 
Player of the Year. Like Collins, she signed early with UCLA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
