<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASEBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SMITHS HELP MOORPARK MOVE INTO WSC LEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Twins Dan and Don Smith led a 17-hit attack Thursday as host Moorpark College 
pounded Santa Barbara, 10-2, and took sole possession of first place in the 
Western State Conference. 
</P>
<P>
Dan Smith, the Raiders' shortstop, went four for six with a run batted in, and 
Don Smith, an outfielder, was three for five, with two RBIs, a double and a 
home run. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark (17-7, 12-3 in WSC play) is a half-game ahead of Cuesta in conference 
play; Canyons, which began the day tied with Moorpark for first, was rained 
out. 
</P>
<P>
Darin Furlong, Henry Schelb, Mike Suarez and Darren Aurand each had two hits 
for the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
John Dickenson, a freshman from Camarillo High, struck out five and allowed 
four singles in eight innings to improve to 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
In other games: 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard 11, Pierce 8 (10 innings) -- Pat Avila of Oxnard slammed a three-run 
home run on the first pitch from reliever Juan Soriano with two on in the 10th 
inning to decide a WSC game at Pierce. 
</P>
<P>
Pat Fairly of Pierce hit his second home run of the day, a two-run shot, in the 
ninth to tie the score, 8-8. Pat Huston doubled and homered for Pierce (11-17, 
4-10). 
</P>
<P>
Cuesta 4, Valley 3 -- Valley took a 2-0 lead in the first on E. J. Pape's 
two-run double, but the Monarchs failed to make the lead stand. 
</P>
<P>
Cuesta (11-3 in conference play) scored three runs in the sixth off starter 
Colin Hines and reliever Dan Carroll, and added another in the ninth off Steve 
Trainor. 
</P>
<P>
Kevin Thomas was four for five for Valley (10-16-2, 7-7). 
</P>
<P>
Azusa Pacific 11, Cal Lutheran 3 -- Peter Washington had three hits, including 
a two-run homer in the third, to lead Cal Lutheran (16-10, 7-6) in an NAIA 
District 3 game at Azusa Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
Bo Rodriguez hit a three-run home run in the second inning for Azusa Pacific 
(19-9, 14-2). 
</P>
