<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One-Year T-Bill Rates Fall: Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills fell at 
the latest auction. 
</P>
<P>
The Treasury sold $9.8 billion of new bills at an average discount rate of 
7.72%, down from 7.76% at the last comparable auction on March 8. The rates 
were the lowest since Feb. 13, when the one-year bills sold for 7.42%. The new 
discount rate understates the actual return to investors -- 8.32%, with a 
$10,000 bill selling for $9,219.40. 
</P>
</TEXT>
