S.D. DANCE ALLIANCE ANNOUNCES ARTIST AWARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego Area Dance Alliance has announced Round I recipients of this 
year's independent artist grants. 
</P>
<P>
An award of $6,850 for projects new choreographic works will be distributed 
among the following artists: Amelia, Alison Cutri, Lorna Dunn, the team of 
Laurie Lowery and Judith Sharp, Patricia Sandback and Ellen Segal (for works to 
be included on Segal's third annual "Garage Dances" concert), and flamenco 
dancer Yaelisa. 
</P>
<P>
Round II applications are due May 14. Those awards will focus on local dance 
makers working with artists in other disciplines. Call 692-4350 for more 
information. 
