<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLEWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newman's Own Verdict: A jury in Bridgeport, Conn., on Thursday rejected a 
delicatessen owner's claims that he was promised a slice of actor Paul Newman's 
gourmet food companies. The Superior Court jury deliberated five hours over two 
days before deciding that Newman never promised Westport deli owner Julius Gold 
8% stock in the companies, Newman's Own Inc. and Salad King Inc., for the help 
Gold said he provided in launching the businesses. "It's just tragic, all of 
this energy and time could not have been spent in more charitable pursuits," 
Newman said after the verdict was announced. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
