<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GROUP TO STUDY HOW TO REVISE CITY CHARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles Mayor Tom Bradley this week announced the formation of a group to 
study ways to reform the city Charter, including possible term limits for 
elected officials and enlargement of the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
The current Charter was adopted in 1925 and has been amended more than 400 
times, but has never been thoroughly overhauled, Bradley said. 
</P>
<P>
Like the Constitution on the federal level, the Charter spells out the 
fundamentals of city government. Bradley did not endorse any specific reform 
proposals but said a study group will be appointed soon to develop procedures 
for amending the Charter, which is expected to be a lengthy process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
