<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: JAIL ORDERED TO INSTALL GAS RETRIEVAL 
SYSTEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regional air-quality officials have once again ordered the Los Angeles County 
Sheriff's Department to install a gas-retrieval system at a garbage dump at the 
department's jail farm in Castaic. 
</P>
<P>
The South Coast Air Quality Management District hearing board refused Wednesday 
to grant the Sheriff's Department permission to operate the small landfill at 
Peter J. Pitchess Honor Rancho without installing equipment to siphon off 
methane gas generated by rotting garbage. 
</P>
<P>
The AQMD said state law mandates such equipment at all landfills. 
</P>
<P>
Technically, the department had sought a "temporary variance" that would have 
allowed the department to operate the dump legally until the hearing board 
could consider a request for a permanent variance on May 9. 
</P>
<P>
The board's action Wednesday makes it highly unlikely that a permanent variance 
will be granted next month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
