<P>
POLICE FIND BODY OF MAN, 67, IN HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A blood-stained car in a Van Nuys parking lot led police Thursday to a Glendale 
house where a 67-year-old man was found dead, authorities said. "We think it's 
a homicide, but we haven't done an autopsy yet," said Bob Dambacher, spokesman 
for the county coroner's office. 
</P>
<P>
Dambacher said the man's identity was being withheld until his family could be 
notified. He said the man was a resident of a one-story duplex in the 1400 
block of Wilson Avenue where the body was found. Glendale police said the 
investigation originated in a Van Nuys restaurant lot, where Los Angeles Police 
Department officers were summoned to examine a suspicious vehicle at 7 a.m. 
Thursday. The car was registered to a Glendale resident, and officers went to 
the Wilson Avenue residence in an effort to find the car's owner. Officers 
entered the house and found the victim inside, the report said. 
</P>
