<P>
24 GANG MEMBERS HELD IN MURDER PLOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two dozen gang members, including at least one 13-year-old boy, were arrested 
on suspicion of plotting the deaths of rival gang members as revenge for the 
shooting death of their leader, authorities said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Police were anonymously tipped to the revenge plot Wednesday after the funeral 
of Gerald Blockman, a gang leader in his early 20s who was shot to death late 
last month, Sgt. Al Thatcher said. 
</P>
<P>
Police, who received word that the group was meeting in a motel room in the 
11900 block of Washington Boulevard in Culver City, arrived at 5:30 p.m. 
Wednesday at the motel and "found these guys all huddled up in a motel room 
making their plans." 
</P>
<P>
Thatcher said they were ordered to come out of the room unarmed and were 
arrested. 
</P>
