Com Systems Buys TMC: The regional long-distance telecommunications company 
said it completed a $22-million acquisition of Santa Barbara-based TMC 
Communications. "The acquisition of TMC solidifies our position as the largest 
regional inter-exchange (long-distance) carrier in the Western United States," 
said Rex Licklider, Com Systems' chairman and chief executive. He said the 
company contemplates additional expansion through acquisition this year. 
