<P>
KOBE STEEL INCREASES STAKE IN KOMAG INC. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kobe Steel U.S.A. Holdings, a unit of the Japanese steel manufacturer, has 
raised its stake in Komag Inc., the Milpitas, Calif., maker of disks for 
computer drives, from 4.23% to 11.21%, or 1.6 million common shares. 
</P>
<P>
Kobe Steel bought 1 million Komag common shares under a Feb. 6 agreement for 
$20 million in cash, or $20 a share, according to a Securities and Exchange 
Commission filing. 
</P>
