<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BUENA PARK; 
</P>
<P>
MINIMUM SETBACKS, LOT SIZES ESTABLISHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To keep tighter control on the size and type of apartment complexes being built 
throughout the city, the City Council passed an ordinance establishing a 
minimum for lot sizes and setbacks. 
</P>
<P>
The ordinance increases setback requirements -- the area between the structure 
and the street or property line -- from 10 to 15 feet in front, back and side 
yards. It also calls for minimum lot sizes of 12,500 square feet and minimum 
lot widths of 100 square feet. 
</P>
<P>
Moving the building back from the street allows more space for landscaping, 
officials said. The ordinance, which was passed by a unanimous vote, goes into 
effect in 30 days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
