<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP TRACK AND FIELD ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
OCEAN VIEW FRESHMAN GIRL WINS THREE EVENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Christie Engesser won three events and teammates Jennifer Dolstra and Jenny 
Sauter recorded career bests to lead Ocean View High School to a 71-56 victory 
over Huntington Beach in a Sunset League showdown Thursday at Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
The victory moves Ocean View (3-0) into first place in the Sunset League. 
Huntington Beach is 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
Engesser, a freshman, won the 800 meters in 2 minutes 36 seconds, the 1,600 in 
5:33 and anchored the 1,600-meter relay team to victory. In the 400, she placed 
second in 1:03.6. 
</P>
<P>
But victories in the field events gave Ocean View an unexpected boost. 
</P>
<P>
Dolstra, who had never long jumped farther than 15 feet 7 inches, won that 
event in 16-8 3/4, and also won the 400 (1:03.3). 
</P>
<P>
Sauter won the high jump at 5-feet, a height she had never previously cleared. 
And the Sea Hawks' Michelle Garay, who has been slowed by injuries most of the 
season, won the triple jump in a season-best 35-3. 
</P>
<P>
"I really felt this would be our toughest meet," Ocean View Coach Beth Chilcott 
said. "We got some luck today, people came through with good marks. I knew the 
field events would be the turning point. And the relays." 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View won the 400-meter relay, as Huntington Beach had a bad exchange on 
the final pass. 
</P>
<P>
Natalie Adam won the 3,200 (12:08) and took seconds in the 800 and 1,600 for 
Huntington Beach, and teammate Noelle Lovin won both hurdle races. 
</P>
<P>
In Sunset League boys' meets: 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 85, Ocean View 47 -- Adrian Brown won the 110 hurdles (14.4), 
the 300 hurdles (41.9), the long jump (22-3) and the triple jump (43-7) to lead 
the Oilers (2-1) at Ocean View. Ben Cesar won the 100 (10.7) and the 200 (22.4) 
for Ocean View (2-1). 
