<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CLARK PITCHES TWO-HITTER IN NO. 1 MATER DEI'S VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jennifer Clark's two-hitter led top-ranked Mater Dei High School to a 2-0 
victory over Bishop Montgomery in an Angelus League softball game Thursday at 
Bishop Montgomery. 
</P>
<P>
Clark (9-0) struck out 11 for Mater Dei (14-2, 3-0). 
</P>
<P>
In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
Foothill 7, El Modena 0 -- Leeann Gonzalez pitched a three-hitter, struck out 
three and walked none, to lead visiting Foothill (8-6, 1-0). Villa Park 3, 
Canyon 1 -- Jen Raworth's two-run triple in the fifth inning broke a scoreless 
tie to lead host Villa Park (7-8-1, 2-0). 
</P>
<P>
In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 1, Los Alamitos 0 -- Beth Howard pitched a two-hitter to lead Cypress 
(14-4, 2-0) at Los Alamitos. Howard (13-2) struck out seven. 
</P>
<P>
In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
Sunny Hills 3, La Habra 2 -- Bernie Fancuberta pitched a four-hitter, striking 
six and walking one, and allowed on earned run for host Sunny Hills (5-9, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 7, Troy 0 -- Cathleen Kennedy (6-4) pitched a one-hitter, and went 
three for four, for Fullerton (8-6, 2-0) at home. 
</P>
<P>
Buena Park 7, Sonora 1 -- Shannon Akau (9-1) struck out 11 and gave up five 
hits for the victory at Sonora. 
</P>
<P>
In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
Santa Margarita 8, Ontario Christian 0 -- Katie Beattie pitched a three-hit 
shutout, striking 12 and walking two to lead host Santa margarita (9-1, 6-1). 
Michelle Mathot had three hits and had five RBIs and stole three bases. 
</P>
<P>
Whittier Christian 3, Capistrano Valley 2 -- Veronica Martinez pitched a 
four-hitter to lead Whittier Christian (8-4, 3-2) at Capistrano Valley 
Christian. Martinez (5-3) struck out seven. 
</P>
<P>
In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
Brea-Olinda 14, Anaheim 5 -- Natalie Stevens had three hits and three RBIs, Kim 
Beck had three hits and Michelle Monroe had three hits and scored four runs to 
lead visiting Brea-Olinda (8-6, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge 12, Orange 0 -- Alisha Nelson (5-7) pitched a three-hitter, striking 
out 11, for Woodbridge (6-8, 2-0) at Orange. 
</P>
<P>
Trabuco Hills 11, Laguna Hills 1 -- Amy Rodriguez, Linda Lunceford and Christy 
Lunceford each homered four host Trabuco Hills (10-4, 2-0). Brianna Durkman 
threw a one-hitter for five innings. 
</P>
<P>
In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor 7, Corona del Mar 2 -- Tina Rodriguez drove in three runs and 
Stacey Giem two to lead host Newport Harbor (4-5, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
Tustin 5, University 0 -- Shannon Ellis (6-3) struck out 10 in a no-hitter. She 
was two outs from a perfect game when a batter reached second base on an error. 
Tustin is 7-4, 2-0. Ellis had two hits and one RBI. University is 6-7, 0-2. 
Saddleback 10, Estancia 0 (4 1/2 innings, mercy rule) -- Desi Abrego pitched a 
no-hitter, striking out 13 and walking none but an error in the fourth inning 
broke up a perfect game. Claudia Rodriguez had two hits and three RBIs to lead 
host Saddleback (11-1, 2-0). Estancia is 1-1 in league. 
</P>
<P>
In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 2, San Clemente 1 -- Erica Koch broke a scoreless tie with a two-out, 
two-run double in the top of the sixth for Irvine (12-2, 2-0) at San Clemente. 
Jennifer Brundage (11-2) pitched a two-hitter, striking out 10, and allowed 
only an unearned run in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 1, Capistrano Valley 0 -- Kerin Dull (10-2) pitched a two-hitter, 
striking out two and walking one to lead visiting Mission Viejo (10-3, 2-0). 
</P>
