TouchStone Software Corp.: The Seal Beach computer software company said it 
lost $52,400 for 1989 due to higher marketing expenditures for a new product. 
</P>
<P>
In 1988, the company posted earnings of $16,300. Revenue in 1989 increased 63% 
to $1.7 million from $1 million the previous year. Shannon Jenkins, president 
and chief executive, attributed the increased revenue to sales of a new 
product. 
