<P>
Photo, Marrow baby -- Anissa Ayala, 18, who suffers from leukemia, holds her 
newborn sister who was conceived to provide bone marrow for a transplant. Baby 
Marissa Eve was discharged from a West Covina hospital today. The transplant is 
months away. See story, B1. JOHN FONTES / San Gabriel Valley Tribune 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
