<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
5 DIE IN SHAM AFGHAN SURRENDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Afghan rebels purportedly surrendering to officials of the Moscow-backed 
government opened fire during a ceremony today in western Afghanistan, killing 
at least five senior military officers, the British Broadcasting Corp. 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
A BBC correspondent recorded the intense sounds of automatic weapons fire used 
during the 15-minute attack in Herat, a city near Afghanistan's Iranian border, 
400 miles west of Kabul. 
</P>
<P>
The reporter said the incident occurred when the provincial governor moved to 
embrace a guerrilla commander, who had apparently voiced his intention to 
surrender with his fighters. 
</P>
<P>
Shooting broke out, prompting a crowd of diplomats, reporters and various 
dignitaries to duck for cover. 
</P>
<P>
The reporter said the governor is in critical condition and "a large number" of 
other officials and some civilians are dead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
