<P>
FAST FOOD TO FT. WORTH BALLET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FT. WORTH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After frying chicken at a fast-food restaurant for several months, Soviet 
ballet dancer Mikhail Gaidamakin debuts tonight with the Ft. 
</P>
<P>
Worth Ballet. 
</P>
<P>
Gaidamakin, 34, defected from the Kirov Ballet during a New York visit in July 
and moved to Dallas, where he lived with his friend Andrei Ustinov, a defector 
from the Moscow Ballet in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
Gaidamakin worked at Grandy's, a chicken joint, before signing with the Ft. 
Worth Ballet in March. He debuts in Glazunov's "The Seasons." 
</P>
</TEXT>
