<P>
SOCCER PASSIONS CLAIM 2 LIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BARCELONA, Spain 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two people were killed in a brawl and 18 were injured in clashes between soccer 
fans and police today after top team Real Madrid's surprise defeat in the 
Spanish Cup final, police said. 
</P>
<P>
They said 18 people were injured here after Barcelona soccer fans celebrating 
their side's unexpected 2-0 win Thursday night in Valencia battled with police. 
Eight people were detained. 
</P>
<P>
Police in Palma de Majorca said a Real Madrid fan and his British girlfriend 
were arrested there today in connection with the death of two brothers in a 
brawl. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the brothers, Jesus and Jose Antonio Lago Ramos, both in their 20s, 
were stabbed to death after an argument over the match. 
