<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
FLOJO EXPECTING 1ST BABY IN FALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Olympic star and world record holder Florence Griffith Joyner is expecting her 
first child in the fall, her business manager said today. "She is expecting 
some time in early November," Gordon Baskin said. 
</P>
<P>
Baskin said Griffith Joyner, popularly known as "FloJo," is delighted with the 
news. "This is something she has hoped for for some time," Baskin said. 
</P>
<P>
Griffith Joyner, 30, set world records in the women's 100 and 200 meters in 
1988 while attracting worldwide attention with her colorful outfits. She won 
three gold medals and a silver at the Seoul Olympics and announced her 
retirement from the sport last year. 
</P>
<P>
Her husband is Al Joyner, the 1984 Olympic triple-jump gold medalist who has 
turned his attention to the 110-meter high hurdles in recent years. 
</P>
<P>
"He's even more excited than Florence," Baskin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
